We’re all just figuring things out as we go. 

I’d personally like to see a 40 over 40, 50 over 50, 60 over 60, etc. To show that age is arbitrary and you can still do amazing things even after your “prime” or whatever that is. Ageism is still a thing and it shouldn’t be.

Are there people on those lists who are like us and didn’t have those same resources? Sure. But they’re anomalies. So don’t beat yourself if you didn’t do it just like them. 

Life isn’t a contest. None of us know all the answers. None of us know what we’re doing. 

3/

That most of us just don’t have access to. Resources we don’t have access to. Connections we don’t have access to. Financial help we don’t have access to. 

Not to undermine what they’ve accomplished, but to allow the rest of us to give ourselves grace. 

2/
